The Foo Fighters played at an election night party for fictional Democratic presidential candidate Matt Santos on an episode of "The West Wing."
This episode did not show an inauguration concert.

On the evening of Jan. 20, 2021, actor Tom Hanks hosted a "Celebrate America" event in honor of U.S. President Joe Biden's inauguration. The event featured a number of musical performances from acts such as the Foo Fighters, Jon Bon Jovi, and Yo-Yo Ma.

As the concert was underway, some people noticed that many of the musical acts at the real "Celebrate America" event, such as the Foo Fighters, had also performed in the fictional universe of the NBC show "The West Wing," which first aired in 1999.
Turns out, the Foo Fighters were truly featured in an episode of "The West Wing." While this is certainly an interesting coincidence, it's not a completely direct parallel.

On "The West Wing," Foo Fighters played their song "Resolve" for an election night concert for fictional Democratic presidential candidate Matt Santos. In the real world, they played their song "Times Like These" (see video above) for an inauguration concert for Biden.

Foo Fighters weren't the only Biden/West Wing crossover act. Biden's inaugural concert also featured performances from Bon Jovi and Ma, both of whom also appeared in episodes of "The West Wing."
